    "body": "## Current situation (pre 1.14.0)\r\nIn order to NOT build plugins for C#, Node, Objective C, PHP, Ruby and Python the only way (I am aware of) is to manually patching the CMakeList.txt on the fly in order to NOT build some or all plugins.\r\n\r\nThis might look like https://github.com/inexorgame/conan-grpc/blob/da3e8a1de7bd391fc3649964bc155891c96c188c/conanfile.py#L40\r\n\r\nThis is constantly breaking with changes in the CMakeList.txt in new gRPC releases.\r\n\r\n\r\n## Situtation with 1.140\r\n1.14.0 introduces the CMake variable `gRPC_BUILD_CSHARP_EXT` which I can simply set to `OFF` in order to NOT build the C# ext. This also doesn't require anymore to patch manually the CMakeList.txt file (at least for this ext), which makes it a lot more reliable, stable and future-proof.\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/252d3f3b460cf56db2e30d68e566a00cef0304eb/CMakeLists.txt#L42\r\n\r\nThis might look like https://github.com/inexorgame/conan-grpc/blob/da3e8a1de7bd391fc3649964bc155891c96c188c/conanfile.py#L73\r\n\r\n## What I wish for with this issue\r\nPlease introduce variables for all plugins which toggle the building or not building of the individual plugin:\r\n  * grpc_ruby_plugin\r\n  * grpc_node_plugin\r\n  * grpc_objective_c_plugin\r\n  * grpc_python_plugin \r\n  * ... and all other parts of grpc which aren't necessary required\r\n \r\n\r\n"
  },
