    "body": "@Croydon   \"plugin\" and \"extension\" are two completely different things.  the \"grpc_*_plugin\" (there's grpc_csharp_plugin too btw) are executables that are plugins for code generating grpc stubs using protoc (the protocol buffer compiler).\r\n\r\nThe grpc_csharp_ext is a completely different beast - it's the native library loaded by C# that provides the RPC functionality implemented in gRPC C core. A normal user doesn't need to know about grpc_csharp_ext at all, it's basically an implementation details of gRPC C#.\r\n\r\nBtw, the cmake file defines various meta targets to build - you don't necessarily need to build all the targets defined in the file, you can choose which target you want to build (e.g. just `libgrpc++`)\r\nExamples: \r\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/a93fdfce84533eeb26461d2d457256df43dd8078/CMakeLists.txt#L2738\r\nhttps://github.com/grpc/grpc/blob/a93fdfce84533eeb26461d2d457256df43dd8078/CMakeLists.txt#L192\r\nWhy is that not sufficient for your needs?\r\n"
  },
